page.title: 15Birds 1-Coleshill.
page.content: The most interesting species which probably breed each year are: Sparrow Hawk Kestrel Lapwing Snipe Woodcock Redshank Collared Dove (New species in the area in 1968,but now breeds in villages and large gardens extensively.) Barn Owl Little Owl Tawny Owl Green Woodpecker Great Spotted Woodpecker Lesser Spotted Woodpecker Goldcrest Treecreeper Spotted Flycatcher Redpoll (A species which has moved into the area from the North in the last 20 or 30 years) Other species seen in the area regularly include: Grey Herron Curlew Kingfisher
